Why CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 instead of MIT:

The previous MIT license allowed anyone to take this guide, modify it,
sell it commercially, repackage it into a paid security course, or
distribute it without attribution. MIT provides no protection against
any of that.

CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 means:

  - Nobody can sell this guide or profit from it in any form
  - Anyone who shares it must credit DresOS
  - Anyone who adapts it must release their version under the same
    license so the community always benefits
  - The DresOS name and work stays protected from commercial exploitation

